<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-10-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                    <head>No. 142.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Morton</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-10-01"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 1,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 359.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to previous correspondence
                        concerning the international conference for the protection of submarine
                        cables, and particularly with reference to the telegram of the Department of
                        the 21st ultimo, authorizing you and Mr. Vignaud to attend the cable
                        conferences and conclude the convention, I now inclose herewith the
                        necessary full powers in the premises.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>[Incloses full powers, as above.]</p>
                    </postscript>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>